					<div id="billing-content" class="kcontent">
						<p class="auSubHeader">Premium Accounts</p>
						<p class="auTextBlock">For a subscription fee, Kerio offers You the option of increasing Your account storage space beyond the initial free offering by converting to a Premium Account. The subscription fees are provided at the <a href="?pricing" class="auLoc-link">Pricing Tab</a>, unless otherwise agreed upon with us in a separate writing. The pricing stated excludes all taxes or other charges that may be applied to Your transaction by local government agencies. You are also responsible for any incidental 3rd party charges for using the Samepage, e.g., charges for Internet access, data roaming, and other data transmission charges. Please note that Your subscription fees are subject to change at any time, without notice, although we will attempt to notify You by email.</p>
						<p class="auSubHeader">Billing and Payment</p>
						<p class="auTextBlock">Converting to a Premium Account requires You to provide a valid credit card for payment purposes. On the day You upgrade to Your Premium Account, You will receive Your first invoice and Your credit card will be charged. Thereafter, on the day before each subsequent subscription anniversary date, Kerio will automatically charge your credit card, on a monthly, quarterly or annually basis  depending upon which billing option You select, unless and until You cancel Your Premium Account. You will also receive a new invoice each time You make changes to Your account. It is Your responsibility to keep Your account information current and updated.</p>
						<p class="auTextBlock">You acknowledge that the amount billed each month, quarter or year may vary for reasons that include but are not limited to differing amounts due to promotional offers, changes in Your subscription fee pricing, and changes in Your account (e.g., adding users and extra storage); You authorize us to charge Your credit card for such varying amounts. Kerio’s general policy is that all fees and charges are nonrefundable and that there are no refunds or credits for partially used periods; exceptions to this policy will be addressed with on a case-by-case basis.</p>
						<p class="auTextBlock">If any subscription fees are not paid in a timely manner, or we are unable to process Your transaction using the credit card information provided, we reserve the right to suspend access to and/or terminate Your Premium Account. However, we will promptly notify You of any payment or past due balance issues via email, and of our intent to take negative action regarding Your Premium Account before doing so. We also reserve the right to assess a late charge on any unpaid balance, at the rate of the lesser of 1% of such balance or the maximum rate permitted by law. To the extent that we are unable to collect unpaid balances from You, we may use a third party to seek collection. You agree to pay for all reasonable costs we incur regarding such collection efforts, including but not limited to reasonable attorneys' fees and other legal fees and costs.</p>
						<p class="auSubHeader">Cancelling Your Account</p>
						<p class="auTextBlock">Your Premium Account will continue in effect unless and until You cancel it or we terminate it. You must cancel Your Premium Account before it renews each month, quarter or year in order to avoid billing of the next period's fees to Your credit card. If You wish to cancel Your Premium Account You may do so by contacting <a href="/help/" class="auLoc-link">Customer Support</a>.</p> 
						<p class="auTextBlock">By signing up for a Kerio Premium Account and providing Kerio with Your payment information, You hereby agree to these Billing Terms.</p>
						<p class="auFinePrint">For further information regarding Your Premium or Free Account, please see the <a href="/cloud/terms/?tos" class="auLoc-link">Samepage Terms of Service</a>.</p>
