					<div id="tos-content" class="kcontent">
						<p class="auSubHeader">Samepage Terms of Service</p>
						<p class="auTextBlock">Welcome to Samepage! These terms of service (“Terms”) form an agreement between You (“You”, Your”), and any organization You represent, and Kerio Technologies Inc. (“Kerio”, “we”, “us” or “our”). By clicking the box below and/or by any usage of our hosted document collaboration services, You agree that these Terms govern Your access to the Samepage website (the “Website”) and Your usage of our services, the software embedded in the Services (the “Software”), the downloadable software available for utilization with the Services (the “Clients”), and any associated documentation (the Website, the services and the Software and Clients are collectively referred to herein as the “Services”). If You are subscribing on behalf of any organization and You are NOT its authorized legal representative or if You do not agree with the Terms as discussed below (to include the terms provided in the associated agreements and policies referenced below), do NOT click the Kerio below and abandon the signup process. </p>
						<p class="auSubHeader">About Samepage</p>
						<p class="auTextBlock">Samepage is a cloud hosted document collaboration solution which allows You to upload, store, share and process data, files, materials text, audio, video, images and other content (“Content”) online. Samepage is offered in both a free and a paid version (aka a “Free Account” and a “Premium Account”). A description of each of the account options, to include features, capabilities and limitations included therein and pricing terms for a Premium Account are provided under the “Pricing” tab. You may also download (i) the Samepage desktop client to allow You to synchronize Your files in the cloud from Your desktop device; and (ii) and our mobile client to allow You to effectively access Your Samepage account from Your mobile device.</p>
						<p class="auSubHeader">Using our Services</p>
						<p class="auTextBlock">To begin using the Services, You are required to create a Free Starter Plan Account with Kerio (become a "Registered User"), by completing a registration form and designating a user ID and password. Until You apply for and are approved by Kerio to become a Registered User, Your access to the Services is limited. When registering with Kerio You must: (a) provide true, accurate, current and complete information about Yourself as requested by the Services’ registration form (such information being the "Registration Data") and (b) maintain and promptly update the Registration Data to keep it true, accurate, current and complete. Kerio may withdraw such approval at any time in its sole discretion, with or without cause.</p>
						<p class="auTextBlock">Only You may use Your account. You must keep Your account and password confidential. You must contact us right away if You suspect misuse of Your account or Your Content or if if You suspect any security breach in the Services. You are responsible for all activities that take place with Your account. Kerio will not be liable for any loss or damage arising from any unauthorized use of Your account.</p>
						<p class="auTextBlock">If a third party such as an employer, or school gave You Your account, that party has rights to Your account and may (i) manage Your account, reset Your password, or suspend or cancel Your account;(ii) view Your account's usage and profile data, including how and when Your account is used; and (iii) read or store Content in Your account. </p>
						<p class="auSubHeader">Levels of Service</p>
						<p class="auTextBlock">Kerio will provide guaranteed levels of service, with rights and remedies as described in the Samepage Service Level Agreement (“<a href="/cloud/terms/?sla" class="auLoc-link">SLA</a>”). The SLA is subject to change at any time without notice, although Kerio will make reasonable efforts to provide two weeks notice (but preferably thirty (30) calendar days if at all possible) to You on this Website.</p>
						<p class="auSubHeader">Acceptable Use of the Services</p>
						<p class="auTextBlock">Access to and use of the Services by You is governed under these Terms and the Samepage Acceptable Use Policy (the "<a href="/cloud/terms/?aup" class="auLoc-link">AUP</a>"). We retain the right to block or otherwise prevent delivery of any type of file, email or other communication to or from the Services as part of our efforts to protect the Services, protect You and our customers, and/or stop You from breaching these Terms. We may also suspend or terminate Your Account at any time without notice if You violate the AUP.</p>
						<p class="auSubHeader">Content</p>
						<p class="auTextBlock">You are solely responsible and liable for Your Content, which we define as any Content You upload, store, process and/or share or any Content that is shared with You. You will: (a) be solely responsible for the nature, quality and accuracy of the Content; (b) ensure that the Content (including the storage or transmission thereof) complies with these Terms and any and all applicable laws; (c) promptly handle and resolve any notices and claims relating to the Content, including any notices sent to You by any person claiming that any Content violates any person's rights, such as take-down notices pursuant to the Digital Millennium Copyright Act and any other notices; and (d) maintain appropriate security, protection and backup copies of the Content, which may include, Your use of additional encryption technology to protect the Content from unauthorized access.</p>
						<p class="auTextBlock">You own Your Content. You represent and warrant that: (a) You have all the rights in the Content contained in Your Account; and (b) the storage, use or transmission of the Content doesn't violate any law or these Terms. Except for material that we license to You, we don't claim ownership of any Content that is transmitted, stored, or processed in Your account. We also don't control, verify, or endorse the Content that You and others make available on or from Your account using the Services.</p>
						<p class="auTextBlock">We provide functions that allow You to control who may access Your Content. If You enable the features that allow You to share the Content with others, anyone You've shared content with (including the general public, in certain circumstances) may have access to Your Content.</p>
						<p class="auTextBlock">You hereby grant Kerio, its employees and agents the right, to use, modify, adapt, reproduce, distribute, display and disclose Content posted on Your Account solely to the extent necessary to provide the Services or as otherwise permitted by these Terms.<br />Kerio has no liability of any kind as a result of the deletion of, correction of, destruction of, damage to, loss of or failure to store or encrypt any Content.</p>
						<p class="auSubHeader">Content Stored Elsewhere</p>
						<p class="auTextBlock">By using and accessing the Services, You understand and consent to the storage and processing of Your Content and any other personal information outside of the country where You are located and utilizing the Services from. However, as discussed in more detail in our <a href="/cloud/terms/?privacy" class="auLoc-link">Privacy Policy</a>, Kerio does abide by the safe harbor framework set forth by the U.S. Department of Commerce regarding the collection, use, and retention of personal information.</p>
						<p class="auSubHeader">Fees and Billing; No Refunds</p>
